postcontent: For sale, factory packed in the original crate, 1200 rounds of Canadian C77 62 grain 5.56 NATO, 600 rounds each in two 50 caliber cans, on ten round stripper clips in Canadian bandoleers. Canadian C77 is equivalent to SS109 and M855 cartridge and is NATO qualified 5.56 X 45 mm Ball cartridge. Its projectile comprises a hardened steel penetrator and lead core in a gilding metal jacket. The maximum chamber pressure is well below the maximum NATO limit, ensuring that the ammunition is safe to use. The C77 cartridge functions properly in all NATO nominated weapons. • Nominal Muzzle Velocity : 2985 f/s • Nominal Bullet Weight : 62 grains • Muzzle Energy : 1,100 foot-pounds (minimum) • Accuracy: 8” maximum standard deviation at 550 m. • Penetration • 1020 steel plate (Hardness = 50/70 Rb; thickness = 1/8”) at 570 m Canadian C77 ammunition is identical to US M855 and SS109 ammo, tips are not painted green, as Canada only used the SS109 spec ammo at the time, did not use the 55 grain M193 and there was no need to paint the tips green to differentiate it from other 5.56 NATO ammunition.$650 cash only, no trades, FTF Frisco, Texas.
